As our church goes into our yearly Pursuit Week, it's important to understand why we fast. Throughout the Bible, there are countless examples of people fasting as a way of surrendering their desires and distractions to the Lord. Let us follow their lead in paving the way to answered prayers this year.

We are expectant and ready for God to move in a mighty way as we dive into Pursuit Week together! We believe that the power of our church is in the power of our prayers. We hope to see you tonight as we kick off four days of fasting, prayer, and powerful worship. Swipe for more information! 🙌⁠
Each day is a gift, so we must treat it with urgency and a great hunger for the Lord. Run after His presence and watch Him move in your life this year.
Because we have been equipped, we are conduits of the supernatural power of God! When we have an urgent spirit and run after Him, we armor ourselves with what He has given us.
Night 3 of Pursuit Tonight @txcelebration! Without prayer we are without Gods Power! The effective prayer of the righteous accomplishes much!

Prayer is a life-long conversation with the Father. When we rest and trust in Him, we find our strength. He sees our quiet places and hears the prayers of His people. This year, let us commit to a life of prayer and constant communication with our Creator. Let our hunger for the Almighty be abundantly greater than any desire for authority.

Tickets are on sale now, so click the link in our bio to secure your spot. Invite a friend, and we will see you at Man Night!

This morning, we got to hear an incredible word surrounding our values as Christ-followers, and the power of a Biblical worldview. 

See you at our 5pm service!

Your values will shape your view. 👀 ⁠
⁠
Your view will determine the way you should walk. 🚶‍♂️⁠
⁠
The way you walk will reflect your heart’s desires. 🤍⁠
⁠
When we walk in Christ and learn from him, our walk will reflect the heart of God. And these things matter not only for today, but for future generations and eternity. ⁠

Swipe 👉 to see where we are taught to place our values as followers of Jesus.

How can we have a pure heart at Christ’s return? We turn our hearts to Christ. 

If we want to see perfection, we must allow the perfection of Jesus to work in us as we hold onto the hope of His appearing. 

“And everyone who has this hope fixed on Him purifies himself, just as He is pure.” (1 John 3:3)

Starting next week, all small groups will be diving into a brand new "Jesus" series. We hope you're inspired to grow in the knowledge of who Jesus is, in your relationship with him, and in your confidence to share His Good News with others! ⁠

⁠
God is interested in the purity of our hearts.⁠
⁠
When we experience the love of Christ, something doesn’t happen TO us, something happens IN us.

If we want to be acquainted with Christ in glory, we must choose hard now! 

It’s easy to choose the wrong way. Let us confidently and boldly pick up our cross and  choose the right way, even in the midst of difficulties and trials.

Let’s remember today that God’s plans are beyond our understanding, and they are so 👏 much 👏 better. ⁠

His gift extends beyond salvation. He desires that we know the abundance of a life fully surrendered to Christ. We can be fully furnished and equipped, because He didn’t just come to bring us out of death but into LIFE. 

You weren’t meant to just go into Heaven, you were meant for Heaven to go into you! 

“In Him was life, and the life was the Light of men.” - John 1:4

Baptisms are a public declaration of your faith. We celebrate with those who took that step to be baptized this Sunday!

“Go, therefore, and make disciples of all the nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit, teaching them to follow all that I commanded you; and behold, I am with you always, to the end of the age.” Matthew 28:19-20

Luke 12:13-34 tells the story of a man who was devoted to increasing his riches on earth. He believed he was secure in his material possessions. God’s response to him was this: “You fool! This very night your soul is required of you; and now who will own what you have prepared?’ So is the man who stores up treasure for himself, and is not rich toward God.”

From this man we learn to use the treasure that God has given us as a testimony to this world. 🌍
